result.execSummary:
The defendant Luis J Yambo was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Vehicle Operator Flee/Elude Officer, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.04(3).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Luis J Yambo in court with attorney Ann M Heaps.  Kimberly Dorice Schoepp appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy court clerk ccp.
Case set for plea and sentencing hearing. Sworn as Interpreter: Enrique Barbosa. State placed negotiations on the record. Plea hearing proceeded.
Defendant sworn in.

As to COUNT 1-
Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, and plead GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum, and Jury Instructions received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain the plea.  Court found the defendant guilty.  Judgment of conviction entered.
  
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess any gun or other firearms. 
Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended, and may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored.  

Court advised defendant if he is not a citizen of the United States of America, that upon a plea of guilty or no contest for this offense, he could be deported, excluded from admission to his country, or denied naturalization under federal law.  
Court advised that the defendant will have to provide a DNA sample, to the Wisconsin State Crime Laboratory for DNA testing and pay a DNA surcharge.

Defendant Luis J Yambo in court with attorney Ann M Heaps.  Deann L Heard appeared on behalf of Kimberly Schoepp for the State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Heaps is now the attorney of record, substituting in as counsel of record, for Attorney Renden.  Attorney Heaps speaks fluent Spanish.   Defense counsel requested a plea and sentencing date after mid-September, as she will be out on maternity leave.  Parties were advised in writing, to which defense counsel advised her client in Spanish, that as of August 1, 2015, this calendar will be transferred to the Hon. Stephanie G. Rothstein, Branch 25, in Room G55 of the Criminal Justice Facility.  All conditions of bail continue.  Agreed Upon Request for a New Court Date is signed and filed.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for October 8, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Luis J Yambo in court with attorney Gregory A. Renden.  Kimberly Dorice Schoepp appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Sworn as interpreter:Brenda Bartholomew. Defense Counsel informs the Court that the Defendant has requested a Spanish Interpreter for court proceedings. 
Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the state:Mark Peterson-MPD Detective.  State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and pleads not guilty.  Case is adjourned to Branch 20.  Scheduling conference scheduled for July 22, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
Cooperate fully with the Children's Court case. And no driving without a valid driver's license. Make all court appearances in both courts.

Defendant Luis J Yambo in court with attorney Gregory A. Renden.  Chad Wozniak appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Moroney, Branch 20. Defendant given a copy of complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed complaint and found probable cause to hold defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT DOES QUALIFY FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.  Case is adjourned for a Preliminary Hearing in Branch PE.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for June 23, 2015 at 08:30 am.
SUMMONS MAILED. DEFENDANT ORDERED INTO ROOM 221 SAFETY BUILDING ON 6/15/15 @ 1:30pm
